{{One source|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox company | name = Aqualand | logo = Aqualand.png | foundation = 1983 | area_served = Europe | location = [[Spain]] | num_locations = 15 | industry = Water Park operator | products = Water parks | parent = Aspro Ocio S.A. | homepage = {{Official website|http://www.aqualand.es/}} }}
'''Aqualand''' is a chain of water-amusement parks operated by Spanish tourism group [[Aspro Parks|Aspro Ocio S.A.]]. It is the largest such group operating in Europe.
Overall there are five Aqualands in [[Spain]] and one in [[Portugal]],<ref name="brand_es"/> eight in [[France]] and one in the [[Netherlands]].<ref name="brand_fr"/> Aspro Ocio also owns a number of other differently branded properties including [[Las Águilas Jungle Park]] on [[Tenerife]].
==Spain== *Aqualand Costa Adeje, [[Tenerife]] *Aqualand Bahía de Cadiz, [[Andalucia]] *Aqualand el Arenal, [[Mallorca]] *Aqualand Torremolinos, [[Malaga (province)]] *Aqualand Maspalomas, [[Gran Canaria]]
==Portugal== *Aqualand Algarve
==France== *Aqualand Agen *Aqualand Bassin D'Arcachon *Aqualand St Cyprien *Aqualand Cap D´Agde *Aqualand [[Saint-Cyr-sur-Mer]] *Aqualand Frèjus *Aqualand Ste Maxime *Aqualand Port Leucate
==Netherlands== *Aqualand Harderwijk
