{{Infobox person | name = Brittany Lauda | image = | other_names = Bree Faith | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1993|02|18|mf=y}} <!-- posted on Facebook public profile --> | birth_place = [[Huntington, New York]], U.S. | education = [[State University of New York at Geneseo]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]], 2014) | residence = [[New York City]], New York, U.S. | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Voice actress, ADR director and producer | spouse = {{marriage|Matt Shipman|2015}} | URL = http://www.brittanylauda.com }}
'''Brittany Lauda''' (born February 18, 1993) is an American voice actress and voice director who has appeared in English language dubs of Japanese anime shows as well as video games.<ref name="facebook">{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/BrittanyLaudaVO/info?tab=page_info|title=Brittany Lauda - Voice Actress|author=|date=|work=facebook.com|accessdate=13 June 2016}}</ref> Her debut role was in ''[[Queen's Blade Rebellion]],'' where she voiced Mirim.<ref name="bio">{{cite web|url=http://brittanylauda.com/wordpress/about-brittany/|title=About Brittany – Brittany Lauda|author=|date=|work=brittanylauda.com|accessdate=13 June 2016}}</ref> She has been involved in many productions from [[Media Blasters]]. Some of her major roles are Plug Cryostat in ''[[Fight Ippatsu! Jūden-chan!!]]'', Audrey in ''[[HuniePop]]'', Cammot in ''[[Holy Knight]]'', Osana Najimi in ''[[Yandere Simulator]]'', and Ui Wakana the title character in ''[[My Wife is the Student Council President]]''. She and fellow voice director Melanie Ehrlich had a production company called MB VoiceWorks which worked on the dub for ''Holy Knight'' and casting for ''[[Ladies versus Butlers]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fandompost.com/2016/05/16/mb-voiceworks-closing-down/|title=MB VoiceWorks Closing Down|author=|date=16 May 2016|work=fandompost.com|accessdate=9 August 2016}}</ref> <!-- NEED SOURCE She also voices in several Hasbro apps and games for the iPhone, including ''[[My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic]]''. --->
Lauda graduated from [[Harborfields High School]] in [[Greenlawn, New York]], and the [[State University of New York at Geneseo]] with a bachelor's degree in history.<ref>Where Are They Now Program, Harborfields Library: http://evanced.info/harborfields/evanced/eventsignup.asp?ID=18024</ref><ref>http://www.harborfieldslibrary.org/adobe/oct14news.pdf</ref> She has also been an active [[cosplay]]er at anime and science fiction conventions under the name '''Bree Faith''' and she is married to fellow voice actor, Matt Shipman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acparadise.com/acp/display.php?a=74366|title=Cosplayer Bree - ACParadise.com|author=|date=|work=acparadise.com|accessdate=13 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://patch.com/new-york/huntington/cosplay-sunday-presented-by-sparkboom|title=CosPlay Sunday (Presented by SPARKBOOM)|author=|date=|work=patch.com|accessdate=13 June 2016}}</ref>
