{{Infobox album | name = Higher Learning Vol.2 | type = Mixtape | artist = [[Fashawn]] | cover = Higher Learning Vol.2 (mixtape).jpeg | alt = | released = {{start date|February 16, 2011}}<ref name="itunes">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/higher-learning-vol.-2-deluxe/id513477289 |title=iTunes: Fashawn "Higher Learning Vol. 2" |publisher=itunes.com}}</ref> | recorded = | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]] | length = | label = [[XXL (magazine)|XXL]] | producer = | prev_title = | prev_year = | next_title = | next_year = }}
'''''Higher Learning Vol.2''''' is a [[mixtape]] by American [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] recording artist [[Fashawn]], released on February 16, 2011. The mixtape is hosted by DJ Ill Will and DJ Rockstar, and presented by [[XXL (magazine)|XXL]] Magazine. It features 22 tracks with appearances by [[J. Cole]], [[GOOD Music]] artist [[GLC (rapper)|GLC]], [[Tony Williams (soul singer)|Tony Williams]], Sam Hook, Gilbere Forte, and more.
The mixtape is particularly known for J. Cole's contributions, which included two vocal appearances and three production credits.<ref name="xxl">{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/xxl-magazine/2011/02/fashawns-higher-learning-2-mixtape-drops-today-download-now/ |title=Fashawn’s Higher Learning 2 Mixtape Drops Today |publisher=xxlmag.com}}</ref> Following the mixtape's release, Fashawn embarked on the Higher Learning Tour with [[Evidence (musician)|Evidence]] and [[Del the Funky Homosapien]].<ref name="tour">{{cite web |url=http://abovegroundmagazine.com/news/tour/01/24/fashawn-announces-higher-learning-tour-dates-with-evidence-more/ |title=Fashawn Announces Higher Learning Tour Dates with Evidence |publisher=abovegroundmagazine.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150217043559/http://abovegroundmagazine.com/news/tour/01/24/fashawn-announces-higher-learning-tour-dates-with-evidence-more/ |archivedate=2015-02-17 |df= }}</ref>
On May 25, 2011, a music video was released for the song "Down That Road", featuring Sam Cooke and produced by Nemis. On June 22, 2011, a music video was released for the song "Big Dreams", produced by J. Cole.
