'''''Marvin the Martian in the Third Dimension''''' (also titled '''''Marvin the Martian in 3D''''' and '''''Marvin the Martian in 4D''''') is a [[3-D film|3-D]] [[Looney Tunes]] film which was formerly an attraction at [[Drayton Manor Theme Park]] in [[Drayton Bassett]], [[Staffordshire]], [[England]], [[Warner Bros. Movie World]] in [[Gold Coast, Australia]], [[Movie Park Germany|Warner Bros. Movie World]] in [[Bottrop, Germany]] (now [[Movie Park Germany]]) and [[Six Flags Great America]]. The movie was the first computer animated movie viewed with 3D glasses to be produced in the world.<ref name="history">[http://korean.movieworld.com.au/about_us/our_history.cfm?history_id=23 Our History ''A Timeline Of Warner Bros. Movie World'' (Official site)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080721213618/http://korean.movieworld.com.au/about_us/our_history.cfm?history_id=23 |date=21 July 2008 }}</ref>
==History== On 26 December ([[Boxing Day]]), 1997, the film opened at Warner Bros. Movie World on the [[Gold Coast, Queensland|Gold Coast]] in [[Australia]]. The attraction opened at the [[Roxy Theatre (Warner Bros. Movie World)|Roxy Theatre]] in Main Street.<ref name="history"/> It mixed the old art of [[Anaglyph image|anaglyphic]] or [[Polarized glasses|polarized]] film (viewed with 3D glasses), and the relatively new art of [[Computer-generated imagery|CGI]] (the first CGI feature-film (Toy Story) was made only 2 years before).<ref name="marvin">[http://www.didik.com/3d_film.htm Directory of 3-D (Stereo) Motion Pictures 1922 - 2001]</ref><ref name="toystory">[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0114709/ Toy Story at the Internet Movie Database]</ref>
In 1997, it was simultaneously screened at the cinema in the Warner Bros. Store in New York. During scenes when Daffy Duck spoke, the audience was sprinkled with water. A large minted token embossed with Marvin the Martian was given on entrance, and could be redeemed for merchandise.
In 2005, the Roxy Theatre saw Marvin the Martian in 3D ending its run and being replaced with [[Shrek 4-D|Shrek 4D Adventure]] which also includes added real world effects to immerse the viewers into the film such as wind, water and smells.
One year later the film began showing at the [[Pictorium]] at Six Flags Great America.<ref>[http://www.sfgamworld.com/attractions/shows.php Unofficial site of Six Flags Great America]</ref> Though, the much larger screen size of the [[Pictorium]] suggests that there may differences from the original film seen in Australia. The version in the Pictorium started showing in 2006 and ceased two years later in May 2008.
In 2011, Drayton Manor announced that they would be replacing [[Happy Feet 4-D Experience]] with Marvin the Martian in 4D. Marvin the Martian began showing at the start of the season on 19 March 2011, and has been there ever since.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nick|title=Drayton Manor to add Marvin the Martian 4D movie for 2011 season|url=http://www.themeparktourist.com/news/20110310/3249/drayton-manor-add-marvin-martian-4d-movie-2011-season|work=10 March 2011|publisher=Theme Park Tourist|accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref>
Later in 2011, this film was released on the [[Looney Tunes Platinum Collection: Volume 1]] Blu-ray. It is not in 3D.
==Plot== The film is based around the two [[Looney Tunes]] characters [[Marvin the Martian]] and [[Daffy Duck]]. "While scanning the universe for signs of hostility, Marvin hears something that sounds like a threat from Earth. Daffy's preparation for his movie role as a dreaded Martian fighter causes the confusion, which results in intergalactic mayhem of comic proportions."<ref name="marvinarchive">{{cite web|url=http://www.movieworld.com.au/rides_attractions/ride_marvin_martian.cfm |title=Warner Bros. Movie World - Marvin the Martian |accessdate=2017-06-04 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20020204093012/http://www.movieworld.com.au/rides_attractions/ride_marvin_martian.cfm |archivedate=4 February 2002 |df= }}</ref> The film is accompanied by various special effects including water and wind which would correspond to screen (e.g. Daffy spitting as he spoke).
==Voices== '''Joe Alaskey''' ''as'' Duck Dodgers, K-9 and Marvin the Martian
