{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}} {{Infobox company | name = Nadeo SASU | logo = NADEO - A UBISOFT STUDIO.png | type = [[Subsidiary]] | industry = [[Video game industry]] | founded = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2000|11|27}} in [[Issy-les-Moulineaux]], France | founder = <!-- or: | founders = --> | hq_location_city = [[Paris]] | hq_location_country = [[France]] | key_people = Florent Castelnerac {{small|([[managing director]])}} | products = ''[[TrackMania]]'' series {{small|(2003–present)}} | parent = [[Ubisoft]] {{small|(2009–present)}} | website = {{URL|nadeo.com}} }}
'''Nadeo SASU''' is a [[French people|French]] [[video game developer]] based in [[Paris]]. Founded on 27 November 2000, the company is best known for developing the ''[[TrackMania]]'' series of video games. On 5 October 2009, it was announced that Nadeo was acquired by French publisher [[Ubisoft]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/116469/Ubisoft_Acquires_TrackMania_Developer_Nadeo.php |title=Ubisoft Acquires ''TrackMania'' Developer Nadeo |first=Kris |last=Graft |date=5 October 2009 |website=[[Gamasutra]] |publisher=[[UBM TechWeb]] |accessdate=12 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://kotaku.com/5374580/ubisoft-buys-trackmania-developers-nadeo |title=Ubisoft Buys TrackMania Developers Nadeo |first=Michael |last=McWhertor |date=5 October 2009 |website=[[Kotaku]] |publisher=[[Gizmodo Media Group]] |accessdate=12 May 2017}}</ref>
Anne Blondel-Jouin served as the company's publishing director between 2011 and 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/shootmania-storm-and-trackmania-2-stadium-coming-steam|title=Shootmania Storm and Trackmania 2: Stadium coming to Steam|publisher=[[PCGamesN]]}}</ref>
