'''Video games in India''' is an emerging market.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/poverty-matters/2013/jul/15/video-game-developers-global-south|title=Game on: how can video game developers in the global south go viral?|first=Dan|last=Griliopoulos|date=15 July 2013|publisher=|accessdate=1 January 2017|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Video game penetration in India is a mere 3%|publisher= [[Daily News and Analysis]]|date=|url= http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report_video-game-penetration-in-india-is-a-mere-3pct_1543478|accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marketresearchworld.net/content/view/5681/76/|title=Indian Video Games Market To Exceed INR 180 Billion By 2018|first=Daniel|last=Sims|website=Marketresearchworld.net|accessdate=2017-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marketresearch.com/product/sample-8758679.pdf |format=PDF |title=India Video Games Market Outlook to 2018 |website=Marketresearch.com |accessdate=2017-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Video-Game Industry Targets New Market: India|publisher= [[Fox News]]|date=|url= http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,297433,00.html|accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Demographics, local tastes fuel Arab video game industry|publisher= Reuters|date=|url= https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/03/14/us-saudi-gaming-idUSBRE82D10N20120314|accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/indian-video-games-industry-grew-16-in-2012/0114217|title=Indian video games industry grew 16% in 2012|website=Mcvuk.com|accessdate=2017-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://techstory.in/gaming-in-india/|title=An Introduction To The Gaming Industry In India ! - TechStory|date=2 February 2016|website=Techstory.in|accessdate=2017-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech-deck/india-a-growing-market-for-game-development-outsourcing/|title=India: A growing market for game development outsourcing|date=15 January 2016|website=Blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com|accessdate=2017-01-02}}</ref> With a turnover of 30 million dollars in 2006, the video game sector is still underdeveloped compared to other Asian countries such as China and South Korea. However, many video game companies are beginning to invest, and India could become an important market for this sector.<ref name="BG33"/>

The Indian gaming market is very varied. While there are a section of hardcore gamers, there are still many gamers playing cartridge games on TV and handheld devices. This has led to the proliferation of pirated, second hand and knock offs to meet the needs of a diverse range of consumers with different access to money and information.<ref>* {{cite journal |last1= Deka|first1= Maitrayee|last2= |first2= |date= 2016|title= Bazaars and Video Games in India|url= http://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1177/0974927616668005?journalCode=bioa|journal= BioScope: South Asian Screen Studies|volume= 7|issue= 2|pages= |doi= |access-date= }}</ref>
With a piracy rate of software and consoles of over 80% and a penetration rate of [[IBM PC compatible|PC]] still low, India's video game market has long lagged behind the rest of World, publishers and distributors of video games struggling to find their place.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gadgets.ndtv.com/games/opinion/gaming-is-a-niche-in-india-because-game-retail-is-broken-754521|title=Gaming Is a Niche in India Because Game Retail Is Broken|website=Gadgets.ndtv.com|accessdate=2017-01-02}}</ref> This delay is also explained by the fact that the country has traditionally never had a real culture of gaming. However, this situation is changing due to the increase in the average income of Indians and the increase in Interest in [[Internet]] and entertainment.<ref name="BG33"/>

Like China and South Korea, India is experiencing strong growth in online gaming. With between 35 and 50 million Internet users, the country is attracting interest from the online video game industry, which is difficult to hack. In October 2005, [[Level Up! Games]] was the first to distribute a [[massively multiplayer online game]] in India with "[[Ragnarok Online]]" and was soon followed by others Companies like Syfy with the game '' [[A3 (video game)|A3]] ''. The latter are South Korean games whose content has been adapted in order to please the people of the country. However, these games were only modestly successful, with about 10000 in 2006. As investments continue to rise, however, the video game market is expected to grow rapidly in India.<ref name = "BG33 ">{{Harvsp | Stang | Osterholt | Hoftun | 2007}}</ref>

One of the factors driving the growth of the video game market is its large number of [[cybercafé]]s with more than 100,000 in 2006, 40% of which are used to play online. Video games play a crucial role in their development by attracting and [[Customer retention|retaining customers]] and, conversely, cybercafes contribute to the promotion of video games. Companies encourage video gaming in india such as mtv do you cypher also niit institutes.<ref name = "BG34">{{harvsp | Stang | Osterholt | Hoftun | 2007}}</ref>

